A case of tuberculous meningoencephalitis in 63-year old man is presented. Symptoms of the disease were found in the course of bone and pulmonary tuberculosis. Attention is paid to diagnostic data that may play an important role in diagnostics of the central nervous system tuberculosis. The therapy of tuberculous meningoencephalitis and the problem of potential Mycobacterium tuberculosis resistance to antituberculous drugs used up to the present are also discussed.